Build a React functional component using Tailwind CSS that replicates a minimal, Apple-inspired horizontal day selector UI.
Layout
Horizontal flex container, center aligned
Each day is a vertical pill-shaped card
Equal spacing between pills
Overall background is very light gray (#F4F4F4)
Pill Design
Width ~64px, height ~96px
Fully rounded corners (rounded-full)
Background: white
Subtle inner shadow for depth
Soft drop shadow for elevation
Content Inside Pill
Top: weekday letter (T, W, T, F, S)
Small uppercase text
Light gray color
Slight letter spacing
Center: large date number
Bold, rounded sans-serif font
Active Day Styling
Active pill contains:
A perfect red circular badge behind the date number
Circle uses a vertical gradient (from-red-600 to-red-400)
Date text is white and bold
Active pill shadow is stronger
Slight vertical lift (-translate-y-1)
Inactive Day Styling
Date number in muted gray
Slight opacity (80â€“90%)
Lighter shadow than active
Shadows
Use soft shadows only:
Inactive: shadow-sm
Active: shadow-lg
No harsh borders
Interactions
Hover:
Slight lift (-translate-y-0.5)
Shadow increases smoothly
Click:
Smooth scale down (scale-95)
Spring back animation
All transitions should use:
transition-all
duration-300
ease-out
Tailwind Rules
No dark theme
No outlines
No gradients except for active red circle
Focus on spacing, softness, and clarity
